This paper is about detecting network anomalies using deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically uses a Variational Autoencoder (VAE) for anomaly detection, which is a type of neural network and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing solutions and proposes a new framework, which involves developing a gradient-based fingerprinting technique for explaining anomalies. This involves using machine learning techniques for interpretability, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework on a dataset, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.SI).
